"body": "Simplified version of https://github.com/bodil/smartstring/issues/7.\r\n\r\nI tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    println!(\"{}\", \"Hello\".to_string() + &(\" World\".to_string()));\r\n}\r\n\r\nstruct FakeString {}\r\n\r\nimpl std::ops::Add<FakeString> for String {\r\n    type Output = Self;\r\n    fn add(mut self, rhs: FakeString) -> Self::Output {\r\n        unreachable!()\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: this should compile correctly.\r\n\r\nInstead, it fails like this:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nerror[E0277]: cannot add `&std::string::String` to `std::string::String`\r\n --> src/main.rs:2:40\r\n  |\r\n2 |     println!(\"{}\", \"Hello\".to_string() + &(\" World\".to_string()));\r\n  |                                        ^ no implementation for `std::string::String + &std::string::String`\r\n  |\r\n  = help: the trait `std::ops::Add<&std::string::String>` is not implemented for `std::string::String`\r\n```\r\n\r\nRemoving the `Add` impl makes it work.\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n\r\nThis is on current stable, 1.46.0.", "closed_by": {"login": "djc", "id": 158471, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE1ODQ3MQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/158471?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc", "html_url": "https://github.com/djc", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/djc/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://a